AIM
To demonstrate Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment (CI/CD) by automating build and deployment processes using Jenkins.
ðŸš€ PROCEDURE
1. Configure Jenkins for CI/CD

Ensure Jenkins is running at:
http://localhost:8080
Log in to Jenkins Dashboard

2. Install Required Plugins
Navigate to:
Manage Jenkins â†’ Plugins

Install:
Git Plugin
Pipeline Plugin
Maven/Gradle plugin (if needed)

3. Create a New Freestyle Project

Steps:

Click New Item
Enter project nam
Select Freestyle project
Click OK

4. Configure Source Code Management (SCM)

Inside your project settings:
Go to Source Code Management
Select Git
Enter your repository URL, e.g.:
https://github.com/your-username/sample-project.git
5. Configure Build Triggers

Choose one:
âœ” Poll SCM
Automatically checks Git repo for changes:

* * * * *

âœ” Build periodically

Schedule automated builds.

âœ” GitHub Webhook

Triggers builds on every push.

Your PDF screenshot (page 3) shows the Trigger settings.
6. Define Build Steps

Go to Build section.

Choose Build Step:

Execute Shell

Execute Windows Batch Command

Invoke Maven Goals

Example Commands:
mvn clean install
javac filename.java
java filename

8. Save and Build

Click Save

Click Build Now

Track build under Build History

9. View Console Output

To see build logs:

Click the build number

Select Console Output

Here you can track:

Git pull process

Compilation results

Test results

Deployment steps
